From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 01:48:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 19/19] pre-message: real mimetype and thumbnail preview in
 metadata

Extend the encrypted Chat-Post-Message-Metadata header so a large-attachment
placeholder can show a real MIME type and a small preview before the
post-message is downloaded.

- PostMsgMetadata gains optional `mime` (from Message::get_filemime(), the
  guaranteed-value accessor: Param::MimeType -> suffix guess -> octet-stream)
  and `thumbnail` (base64 JPEG, longest edge 128px, quality 40, capped at
  20_000 encoded bytes). from_msg builds the thumbnail from the attachment
  blob for Image/Gif/Sticker and from the app icon (get_webxdc_blob) for
  Webxdc; Video/Audio/File get none. Any failure warns and yields None so a
  preview never fails a send.
- blob::thumbnail_base64 does the pixel work in block_in_place, flattening
  alpha onto white before JPEG encode.
- Receive side sets Param::MimeType from `mime` and, after a 60_000-char guard
  on the attacker-controlled base64, stores the thumbnail as a normal blob
  referenced by Param::File. `file` deliberately holds the preview JPEG while
  `fileMime` names the real target mime; the frontend treats `file` as a
  preview until downloadState == Done.
- jsonrpc: get_post_message_viewtype is no longer test-only and MessageObject
  exposes post_message_view_type; naturally None once the post-message arrives.

Wire-compat: the new header fields are optional JSON keys
(skip_serializing_if = Option::is_none); serde ignores unknown keys both ways,
so an old Delta Chat simply drops them and slothful degrades gracefully when
they are absent.

Storage: the thumbnail is a normal blob keyed by Param::File, so housekeeping's
remove_unused_files GCs it once the placeholder is trashed or the arriving
post-message overwrites file/fileMime. No new table, no migration, no hooks.

